## 2. Project Strengths (What is working well)\
\
### A. Architectural Decoupling\
You have successfully separated the *Ingestion Mechanism* from the *Analytics Engine*.\
* **Why it works:** By creating a "Staging Layer" that accepts data from both the current Excel files and the future UI, you future-proof the project. You can completely rewrite the frontend tracker later without breaking a single Power BI report or ML model.\
\
### B. Domain Specificity\
Unlike generic "sports tracker" templates, this project understands hockey nuances:\
* **Logical Shifts:** The logic to collapse consecutive segments into "logical shifts" is critical. Raw data is often messy; this transformation layer handles the reality of tracking errors.\
* **Spatial Granularity:** Distinguishing between `dim_rink_zone` (coarse) and `dim_rink_box` (fine) allows for both high-level coaching insights and detailed ML analysis later.\
\
